Class Commercial

  • java.lang.Object
    • domain.Property
      • domain.Commercial
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Commercial
extends Property
    Version:
    6.26. Concrete class of abstract class Property. We validate all attributes of the property and will throw an exception for the invalid inputs. Waste Management and Fire Services Levy are charged together with CIV value multiplied by a CIV rate.
    Author:
    Anush
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • Commercial

        public Commercial(java.lang.String description,
                  java.lang.String location,
                  double area,
                  double siteValue,
                  double capitalImprovedValue,
                  double capitalImprovedRate,
                  double netAnnualValue,
                  java.lang.String valuationDate,
                  domain.RatePayer owner,
                  java.lang.String businessName,
                  java.lang.String abn)
           throws java.lang.NullPointerException
        Construct a new Commercial Property which inherits all attributes of Property and Commercial class. Instantiate the Property class with its nine-parameter constructor by passing in the Property class attributes. Set the Commercial class attributes based on the values passed in from the parameters. It will throw an exception if any attribute passed in is null or empty.
        Parameters:
        description - A string to define the description of property
        location - A string to define the location of property
        area - A double to specify the area of property in square meters
        siteValue - A double to specify the site value of property
        capitalImprovedValue - A double to specify the Capital Improved Value of property, it should be greater than the site value
        capitalImprovedRate - A double to specify the Capital Improved Rate of property
        netAnnualValue - A double to specify the net annual value of property
        valuationDate - A string to define the valuation date of property
        owner - A RatePayer object to specify the owner of property
        businessName - A string to define the name of the Commercial property
        abn - A string to define the Australian Business Number(ABN) of the Commercial property
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any parameter passed in is null or empty

      • Commercial

        public Commercial()
        Construct a new Commercial property with zero parameter. Instantiate the Property class with its zero-parameter constructor. Assign default values for Commercial class attributes. Set the Capital Improved Rate on the Property class for this property type.
